body:
In a number of places when emitting a construct that's zero-width instead of omitting it we do so but prefix it with `//`.  This is fragile as the emitted text following can often trigger wrapping and cause the output to be invalid.

Example (modified from `hw-dialect.mlir`), `zerowidth-wrapping.mlir`:
```mlir
hw.module @TestZero(%a: i4, %zeroBitWithAVeryLongNameWhichMightSeemUnlikelyButHappensAllTheTime: i0, %arrZero: !hw.array<3xi0>)
  -> (r0: i4, rZeroOutputWithAVeryLongName_YepThisToo_LongNamesAreTheWay_MoreText_GoGoGoGoGo: i0, arrZero_0: !hw.array<3xi0>) {

  %b = comb.add %a, %a : i4
  %c = comb.add %zeroBitWithAVeryLongNameWhichMightSeemUnlikelyButHappensAllTheTime, %zeroBitWithAVeryLongNameWhichMightSeemUnlikelyButHappensAllTheTime : i0
  hw.output %b, %c, %arrZero : i4, i0, !hw.array<3xi0>
}

hw.module @TestZeroInstance(%aa: i4, %azeroBit: i0, %aarrZero: !hw.array<3xi0>)
  -> (r0: i4, rZeroOutputWithAVeryLongNameYepThisToo: i0, arrZero_0: !hw.array<3xi0>) {

  %o1, %o2, %o3 = hw.instance "iii" @TestZero(a: %aa: i4, zeroBitWithAVeryLongNameWhichMightSeemUnlikelyButHappensAllTheTime: %azeroBit: i0, arrZero: %aarrZero: !hw.array<3xi0>) -> (r0: i4, rZeroOutputWithAVeryLongName_YepThisToo_LongNamesAreTheWay_MoreText_GoGoGoGoGo: i0, arrZero_0: !hw.array<3xi0>)
 %c = comb.add %o2, %o2 : i0

  hw.output %o1, %c, %o3 : i4, i0, !hw.array<3xi0>
}
```

Here's the current output of `circt-opt -export-verilog ./zerowidth-wrapping.mlir -o /dev/null`:
```systemverilog
// Generated by CIRCT 1.20.0g20221025_97824a4
module TestZero(	// ./zerowidth-wrapping.mlir:1:1
     input  [3:0]               a,
  // input  /*Zero Width*/      zeroBitWithAVeryLongNameWhichMightSeemUnlikelyButHappensAllTheTime,
  // input  [2:0]/*Zero Width*/ arrZero,
     output [3:0]               r0
  // output /*Zero Width*/      rZeroOutputWithAVeryLongName_YepThisToo_LongNamesAreTheWay_MoreText_GoGoGoGoGo
  // output [2:0]/*Zero Width*/ arrZero_0
   );

  assign r0 = a + a;	// ./zerowidth-wrapping.mlir:4:8, :6:3
  // Zero width: assign rZeroOutputWithAVeryLongName_YepThisToo_LongNamesAreTheWay_MoreText_GoGoGoGoGo = zeroBitWithAVeryLongNameWhichMightSeemUnlikelyButHappensAllTheTime +
                zeroBitWithAVeryLongNameWhichMightSeemUnlikelyButHappensAllTheTime;	// ./zerowidth-wrapping.mlir:5:8, :6:3
  // Zero width: assign arrZero_0 = arrZero;	// ./zerowidth-wrapping.mlir:6:3
endmodule

module TestZeroInstance(	// ./zerowidth-wrapping.mlir:9:1
     input  [3:0]               aa,
  // input  /*Zero Width*/      azeroBit,
  // input  [2:0]/*Zero Width*/ aarrZero,
     output [3:0]               r0
  // output /*Zero Width*/      rZeroOutputWithAVeryLongNameYepThisToo
  // output [2:0]/*Zero Width*/ arrZero_0
   );

  // Zero width: wire /*Zero Width*/ _iii_rZeroOutputWithAVeryLongName_YepThisToo_LongNamesAreTheWay_MoreText_GoGoGoGoGo;	// ./zerowidth-wrapping.mlir:12:19
  TestZero iii (	// ./zerowidth-wrapping.mlir:12:19
    .a                                                                              (aa),
  //.zeroBitWithAVeryLongNameWhichMightSeemUnlikelyButHappensAllTheTime             (azeroBit),
  //.arrZero                                                                        (aarrZero),
    .r0                                                                             (r0)
  //.rZeroOutputWithAVeryLongName_YepThisToo_LongNamesAreTheWay_MoreText_GoGoGoGoGo (_iii_rZeroOutputWithAVeryLongName_YepThisToo_LongNamesAreTheWay_MoreText_GoGoGoGoGo)
  //.arrZero_0                                                                      (arrZero_0)
  );
  // Zero width: assign rZeroOutputWithAVeryLongNameYepThisToo = _iii_rZeroOutputWithAVeryLongName_YepThisToo_LongNamesAreTheWay_MoreText_GoGoGoGoGo +
                _iii_rZeroOutputWithAVeryLongName_YepThisToo_LongNamesAreTheWay_MoreText_GoGoGoGoGo;	// ./zerowidth-wrapping.mlir:12:19, :13:7, :15:3
endmodule
```

With the problematic lines being:

```systemverilog
  // Zero width: assign rZeroOutputWithAVeryLongName_YepThisToo_LongNamesAreTheWay_MoreText_GoGoGoGoGo = zeroBitWithAVeryLongNameWhichMightSeemUnlikelyButHappensAllTheTime +
                zeroBitWithAVeryLongNameWhichMightSeemUnlikelyButHappensAllTheTime;	// ./zerowidth-wrapping.mlir:5:8, :6:3
```

and


```systemverilog
  // Zero width: assign rZeroOutputWithAVeryLongNameYepThisToo = _iii_rZeroOutputWithAVeryLongName_YepThisToo_LongNamesAreTheWay_MoreText_GoGoGoGoGo +
                _iii_rZeroOutputWithAVeryLongName_YepThisToo_LongNamesAreTheWay_MoreText_GoGoGoGoGo;	// ./zerowidth-wrapping.mlir:12:19, :13:7, :15:3
```

I believe the instance port expression can be made to wrap as well, and perhaps others, but haven't pushed on triggering that case.
